Hey guys! Are there any Harry Potter fans here? ⚡️
⠀
I’ve made a compilation of my Harry Potter series which I did in a filled-outline style. Not many of you remember this but I spent years working in that style and I still like it a lot even though I’ve moved away from it 👨‍🎨
⠀
I hope you will like watching this compilation and let me know if you want to see more illustrations in outline style from me. Thanks! 🤗

node.text:
Scarecrow 👁👅👁
⠀
When I shared the WiP of this illustration a few days ago in my stories and asked you to guess who it is, the majority of you thought it would be an onion boy, but it’s a scarecrow 😄
⠀
I had so much fun doing this little buddy! It took me more time to create than I thought in the beginning, that's why I showed some parts of it with a help of Liquify Tool 👻
⠀
I still don't know how to call it, if you have any suggestions please let me know in the comments! 👇

🔸 Gain the highest score in the leaderboards by this Sunday.
🔸 First 3 winners on iOS + 3 winners on Android will get my sticker pack.

The sticker pack includes the game related stickers as well as a few stickers of my classic illustrations ✍️
⠀
On Sunday at 11AM (ET) I will announce the winners in my Instagram stories. Good luck! 🤗
⠀
Also, I would love to hear your feedback on the game, what is good and what is not. If the game survives I am planning to add so much more fun things to it. If you have any ideas I will appreciate if you share it in the comments 👇

I've made a mobile game! 🔥
⠀
Hi friends! Hope you all are doing well!👋 Two days ago I've asked for your thought on what I've been working for the last months and a few people were right - it's a mobile game! 👾
⠀
Congratulations to @apoorvab89 who was the first one who gave the right answer in the comments and won my sticker pack! 🎉
⠀
So here’s the whole story:
⠀
There was a moment a few months ago when I wanted to spice up my routine and work on a new big project so I decided to try myself in creating mobile games. I don’t know if it’s gonna succeed but I enjoyed creating it so much, was really excited and inspired about it this whole time even though the project took 5 months instead of 2 😄
⠀
The game is called Gardentale 🧚 and it’s just been released so I would appreciate an honest feedback from you 🙏
⠀
Also, let me know if you’re interested in learning more about the workflow and process that I used to create the graphics and animations for this game because it took me quite some time and iterations to find the style for this gameplay ✨
⠀
The game is absolutely free and doesn't have any annoying ads! Available fof both Android and iOS. The link is in my profile! 👆

News and free stickers (read till the end) 🔥
⠀
Hey guys! Haven’t done any personal posts in a while. Now after months of intense hard work and chaotic changes, I would like to share what’s been happening with me during past 6 months ☀️
⠀
As you might know I spent the most of this year in Bali, it was a really nice place to spend the quarantine at. While I was staying there I had some time to step back and think about my career and things I like do the most and the new things that I would like to do. And I figured out one thing that I was always passionate about but never had an opportunity to dive into it 🌊
⠀
So in May, I decided to start working on this new project. At first I dedicated  one hour a day to it (during a coffee break), then 2 hours a day and by July it became my 60-hours-a-week hobby 😄 And by August when I knew that soon I would go back home to my old routine I tried to do as much as I could to finish up that project ⚡️
⠀
I flew back home in the middle of August and only by now I’m ready to release that project. To be honest I’m really anxious about what the outcome will be 😅
⠀
Anyway, I hope you don’t mind me putting some mystery on what this project is, I will share all the details on Thursday. But now I’m wondering if anyone can guess what the project is about, first person who guesses it right will get my sticker pack! Please leave your guesses in the comments 👇

Course updates! 🔥
⠀
It’s been 6 months since I’ve released my drawing course. And in this post I would like to share some updates and my thoughts on what’s been happening with the course over this time 💭
⠀
I can see that the structure of the course that I created in the beginning worked out really well, it’s very beginner-friendly and makes you gain new skills fast ⚡️
⠀
Besides one extra chapter (the jellyfish animation 🐠) that I added in May, I haven’t done any dramatic changes to the structure. And that’s great because I could focus on providing some additional useful perks for the course:
⠀
🔸 English subtitles for all the course videos
🔸 Essential Procreate brushes pack
🔸 Source files of my best animations, etc.
⠀
And by now already hundreds of people have completed the course and managed to level up their art skills ✍️
⠀
Also, today I’m happy to announce that I’ve finally added the Russian subtitles as well, it took me quite some time to translate it 😅 I translated it myself (the content size of a decent book) because Russian is my native language and I didn’t want to have a robotic (out-of-context) translation done by Google 🔠
⠀
If you’re still hesitating to take my course thinking that you don’t have any talent to drawing or it would be too hard for you, I can assure you that anyone can learn to draw at least as for a hobby. And to prove my words, check out my free ‘iPad drawing for beginners’ masterclass (you can find it on my website) which will give you an idea how easy it is to get started! 🎨
⠀
And for those of you who already want to enroll to my drawing course “Become a Pro in Procreate”, click on the link in my bio to learn all the details and get a lifetime access to it 🚀
⠀
Thanks for reading till the end, hope you don’t mind me talking about the course from time to time because this project is very important for me and have already put a year of hard-work in it and going to put even more since I found teaching to be a very inspiring and fulfilling interest of mine 😊
